OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1780243866
OL,3,COne in five adults in Wales living
OL,4,Cwith diabetes or prediabetes
OL,6,FOne in five adults in Wales is "living
OL,7,Fwith diabetes or prediabetes", which
OL,8,Fcauses higher-than-normal blood sugars
OL,9,Fand carries a greater risk of
OL,10,Fdeveloping the condition, according to
OL,11,Fnew NHS data.
OL,13,FThe total includes almost 60,000
OL,14,Fpeople who are not yet diagnosed,
OL,15,FPublic Health Wales (PHW) said.
OL,17,FIt is estimated that more than 230,000
OL,18,Fpeople aged 17+ now have the
OL,19,Fcondition, an increase of 7,685 people
OL,20,Fin a single year. Type 2 diabetes
OL,21,Faccounts for most cases.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
