FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1780243866
OL,3,COne in five adults in Wales living
OL,4,Cwith diabetes or prediabetes
OL,6,FThe new figures are higher than had
OL,7,Fbeen predicted, and have prompted the
OL,8,Fhealth agency to urge more people to
OL,9,Ftake immediate action to reduce their
OL,10,Frisk of developing the condition.
OL,12,FPublic Health Wales and Diabetes UK
OL,13,FCymru say, "left unmanaged, (diabetes)
OL,14,Fcan lead to serious complications
OL,15,Fincluding sight loss, kidney disease,
OL,16,Fnerve damage, and cardiovascular
OL,17,Fdisease".
OL,19,FThe condition causes blood sugar
OL,20,Flevels to rise, with two types
OL,21,Fstemming from different causes.
OL,26,@uD@]pmuD@fpn
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/9
