OL,3,COne in five adults in Wales living
OL,4,Cwith diabetes or prediabetes
OL,6,FDavid Taylor, from Public Health
OL,7,FWales, said, "This rapid increase of
OL,8,Fpeople now being diagnosed with Type 2
OL,9,Fdiabetes is a national crisis for
OL,10,FWales, but thankfully it is one we can
OL,11,Frespond to.
OL,26,@oD@NOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1780243866
OL,3,COne in five adults in Wales living
OL,4,Cwith diabetes or prediabetes
OL,6,F"Being diagnosed with Type 2 diabetes
OL,7,Fis never about it being that person's
OL,8,Ffault, but often, if that person had
OL,9,Fhad access to the right information
OL,10,Fand was given the support they needed
OL,11,Fearly enough, then lowering their
OL,12,Frisk, pushing their diagnosis back or
OL,13,Freducing future complications if
OL,14,Fdiagnosed, are all very real
OL,15,Fpossibilities.
OL,17,FRachel Burr, Director of Diabetes UK
OL,18,FCymru, said, "It's important to find
OL,19,Fout whether you're at risk of
OL,20,Fdeveloping type 2 diabetes ` so you
OL,21,Fcan take action to protect your health.
OL,26,@nD@AOUzD@NOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/9
